; Use a combined CA bundle (Node's public Mozilla roots + the Zscaler corporate
; root) so npm works both on the open internet and behind Zscaler TLS inspection.
; The user-level .npmrc sets cafile to the Zscaler cert ALONE, which replaces the
; bundled roots and breaks verification of the real registry chain; this overrides it.
cafile=C:\\Users\\op5805\\.zscaler\\combined-ca.pem
